## Spec-driven development

- When creating a new feature, ensure a spec is generated for the feature
- Each spec will be used to guide the development of a feature
- Break the spec down into small chunks and clarify each chunk before continuing to the next chunk
- Clarify any requirements that are undefined
- Once the spec requirment gathering is complete, prompt with the full text to generate a `.spec.md` file within the `spec` directory of either the workspace (if the feature affects multiple packages) or the appropriate package (if the feature is internal to a single package)
- Once the spec file has been generated, use it to generate the contents of a `README.md` containing usage examples
- Clarify each usage examples before proceeding
- Once the `README.md` is complete, prompt to generate high-level unit tests for the feature
